Privacy Policy
This document delineates the protocols and measures for the handling, utilization, and sharing of your data when you engage with our Platform, detailing your data protection rights and the legal safeguards in place.
Your personal information is leveraged to enhance and deliver the Platform's services. Engaging with the Platform signifies your consent to our data practices as outlined in this document.
Clarifications
· Terms capitalized in this text hold specific definitions provided below. These definitions hold the same significance in both singular and plural forms.
Defined Terms
For this document:
· Account denotes a unique profile established for you to access specific or all areas of the Platform.
· Affiliate describes any entity that has control, is controlled by, or is under shared control with another entity, with "control" denoting ownership of 50% or more of the voting shares or interests.
· Application pertains to the Benjapps Technologies, a software solution offered by our entity.
· Entity (also referred to as "the Entity," "We," "Us," or "Our" within this agreement) relates to Benjapps Technologies, located in Tel Aviv.
· Country signifies: Israel
· Device encompasses any technology capable of accessing the Platform, including but not limited to computers, smartphones, and tablets.
· Personal Information refers to data related to an identifiable individual.
· Platform means the Application.
· Service Provider indicates any person or company that processes data on behalf of the Entity, pertaining to third-party entities or individuals engaged by the Entity to facilitate the Platform, deliver services on behalf of the Entity, or assist in evaluating how the Platform is utilized.
· Usage Information pertains to data accumulated automatically through the use of the Platform or from the Platform's infrastructure itself (e.g., the length of a page visit).
· You identifies the individual using or engaging with the Platform, or the company or legal entity represented by such an individual.
Personal Information
During your use of our Platform, we may request personal details that could be used to contact or identify you. This may include, but is not limited to usage Information:
· Usage Information is gathered automatically through your interaction with the Platform.
· This data may include details such as your Device's Internet Protocol address (IP address), browser type and version, pages of our Platform visited, date and time of visit, time spent on those pages, unique device identifiers, and other diagnostic data.
· Accessing the Platform via a mobile device may lead to the automatic collection of certain data, including your mobile device type, unique mobile device ID, mobile device's IP address, mobile operating system, type of mobile browser, and other diagnostic data.
· Additionally, information sent by your browser when you visit our Platform or access the Platform via a mobile device may be collected.
Information Collected through the Application
· To deliver certain features of our Application, we may collect data with your prior permission from your Device's camera and photo library.
· This data assists in offering Platform features, enhancing and personalizing our services. It may be stored on our servers or those of our Service Providers, or remain on your Device.
· You can manage the access to this information at any time through your Device settings.
Utilization of Your Personal Information
The Entity may use your Personal Information for the following:
· To provide and maintain our Platform, including monitoring its usage.
· To manage your Account, facilitating your use as a registered user with access to different Platform features.
· For contractual performance: developing, complying with, and executing the purchase agreement for products, services, or other contracts made with us through the Platform.
· To contact you via email, phone calls, SMS, or other electronic communications like push notifications from a mobile app regarding updates or informational messages related to functionalities, products, or contracted services, including necessary security updates.
· To offer news, special deals, and general information about other goods, services, and events similar to those you have already purchased or inquired about, unless you choose not to receive such information.
· To handle your inquiries and requests.
· For business restructurings: Your information might be used to assess or carry out mergers, acquisitions, restructurings, dissolutions, or other asset transfers.
For additional purposes: Your information may be used for data analysis, identifying usage trends, evaluating promotional campaign effectiveness, and enhancing our Platform, products, services, marketing, and your overall experience.
· We may share your personal information under the following circumstances:
· With Service Providers: To monitor and analyze the use of our Platform, and to contact you.
· For business transactions: Your personal information may be shared or transferred as part of negotiations or during the completion of mergers, asset sales, or acquisitions by or with another company.
· With Affiliates: We may share your information with our affiliates, ensuring they adhere to this privacy protocol. Affiliates include our parent company, subsidiaries, joint venture partners, or other companies we control or that are under common control with us.
· With business partners: To offer you specific products, services, or promotions.
· With other users: When you interact in public areas of the Platform, shared information may be visible to all users and could be publicly distributed outside.
· With your consent: We may disclose your personal information for any agreed-upon purpose.
Retention and Deletion of Your Personal Information
· Your Personal Information will be retained only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this document. We may also retain and use your information to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements.
· We also retain Usage Information for internal analysis, which is generally held for a shorter duration unless required for security enhancement, functional improvement of our Platform, or compliance with legal obligations.
Transfer of Your Personal Information
· Your data, including Personal Information, may be processed in any location where our operations or involved parties are based. This may involve transferring data outside your state, province, country, or other jurisdiction, potentially to places with differing data protection laws.
· Your submission and subsequent processing of such information imply your consent to these transfers, under the assurance that your data will be securely handled and in accordance with this document.
· The Entity is committed to ensuring the secure handling of your Personal Information, although no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is completely secure. We aim to use commercially acceptable means to protect your data but cannot ensure its absolute security.
Protection of Minors
· Our Platform does not cater to anyone under the age of 13. We do not intentionally gather personal information from children under 13. If you, as a guardian or parent, become aware that your child has provided us with personal data, please contact us. If we discover that personal data from minors has been collected without parental consent verification, we will take steps to remove such information promptly.
· In jurisdictions where parental consent is required for data processing under the age of consent, we may seek a parent's consent before collecting and using such information.
Links to Other Sites
· Our Platform may include links to external websites not operated by us. If you follow a third-party link, you will be directed to that party's site. We urge you to review the privacy terms of every site you visit.
· We do not control and are not responsible for the content, privacy terms, or practices of any third-party sites or services.
Updates to this Document
· We may revise these data handling terms occasionally. Any changes will be communicated through the updated document posted on this page.
· We will inform you via email and/or a prominent notice on our Platform before changes take effect, updating the "Last updated" date at the bottom of this document.
· We recommend reviewing this document periodically for any changes. Modifications to these terms are effective when they are made available on this page.
